b81a56db-917c-4509-83b0-4e8751ef4b3c.4e622f80-d804-4e04-9922-b7332023a348.description=
Runs a command and allows user to specify that it runs locally (in this case no port should be specified), via ssh, Global Shell, ROSH, Telnet, or RSH.

Inputs\:
host - Hostname or ip address.
port - Port number for connecting to the host.
username - Username to connect as.
password - Password of the user.
protocol - The protocol used to run the command (can be one of ssh, ROSH, GlobalShell, Telnet, RSH, local, WMI, NASConnectTelnet, or HPOM).
timeout - (optional, default 90 seconds) time in milliseconds to wait for the command to complete; increase its value if you are getting incomplete output results or timeout.
command - The command to execute.
arguments - The arguments to pass to the command.
environment - Specifies environment variables/values that need to be defined when running command.
startDir - The path to the starting directory.
pty - Whether to use pty (used by ssh, GlobalShell. Valid values\: true, false).
privateKeyFile - Path to private key file, relative to ICONCLUDE_HOME on RAS host.
sasHost - The host we want to run the ROSH command on.
sasHostUsername - The username used to run the ROSH command on sasHost.
usernamePrompt - The prompt that when seen should send the username; used by the Telnet protocol; when used by the NASConnectTelnet protocol, the default value is 'NAS Login\:'
passwordPrompt - The prompt that when given should send the password; used by the Telnet protocol; when used by the NASConnectTelnet protocol, the default value is 'Password\:'
outputPath - Network accessible path used by the operation to store temporary files. If not specified it points to \\host\admin$\temp\'. If this path is not accessible you should change it to use another share that the host local system account has write access to. By default, the path will have to be  changed on Windows 2000 systems
nasDevice - The NAS device to run the command on when using the NASConnect protocol.
nasDeviceConsoleMode - The NAS device console mode used to run the command scripts that run the command on the given NAS device. If this input is empty, command scripts are not used, and the connection to the NAS device and the command are issued directly in the console; this is not recommended, since its error handling capabilities are limited and it might result in success even when the command fails to execute. The values for this input can be found in the NAS web interface, as a drop-down list when a new command script is created (ex. Cisco IOS enable).
hpomNode - Node on which the command is to be executed.
hpomProtocol - Protocol to communicate with HPOM (http or https).
characterSet - The characterSet name for stream encoding and decoding between the RAS and target machine. For example, SJIS,EUC-JP, UTF-8.  By default it is UTF-8 (used by ssh, GlobalShell, Telnet, RSH).

Responses\:
success - The command was executed successfully.
failure - The command could not be executed.

Extra Results\:
stdErr - The STDERR of the command.
stdOut - The STDOUT of the command.
b81a56db-917c-4509-83b0-4e8751ef4b3c.b2ebc7b5-3e27-4af0-bfd0-a62cc1e3aea8.description=
This operation checks whether a string matches another string, using a specific matching rule. The "toMatch" input is the string that is checked for matching the "matchTo" expression. 

Inputs\:
    matchType - The type of match to perform.
Valid values\: Exact Match, Contains, Contains Once, Does Not Contain, Match All Words, Match No Words, Regex
Default value\: Exact Match
    toMatch - The string that is checked for matching.
    matchTo - The string to match against.
Example\: If "matchType" is “RegEx”, the "matchTo" input is a regular expression such as\: ^-?\d+(([\.,]\d+)?)+$. 
    ignoreCase - Specifies whether to ignore case when matching or not.
Valid values\: False, True
Default value\: False

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the string "Matches" if the "toMatch" string matches the "matchTo" string. Otherwise, it contains the string "Does Not Match".  

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.
b81a56db-917c-4509-83b0-4e8751ef4b3c.c0bbe2bd-3757-4df2-8409-4106d7735059.description=Retrieves the server(s) ServerVO properties Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to Connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for host. corePassword - The password for host. coreVersion - The version of SAS to use. agent - The agent name search string (can be a partial name and multiple return results can be returned; the matching type for this input can be selected by using the 'matching' flag). matching - A flag that indicates if the search performed using the agent name should be based on a partial or exact match. The default value for this input is 'Begins With'. serverID - The ID of the searched server. This input should be used for unique identification. If provided, then the 'agent' input is ignored. delimiter - The delimiter used to separate the result values. By default the values are comma delimited. Responses\: success - retrieved successfully failure - failed to retrieve data Returns\: createdBy - The name of the user who created this object. createdDate - The date that this object was created. id - The unique ID of this object. createdBy - The name of the user who created this object. createdDate - The date that this object was created. dirtyAttributes - A ; delimited list of attributes that are dirty (Modified and not yet fully propagated). modifiedBy - The user who last modified this object. modifiedDate - The date that this object was last modified on. description - The description of this object. hostname - The DNS hostname of this object. model - The model of this object. osVersion - The version of the OS running on the object. primaryIP - The primary IP address of this object. serialNumber - This object's serial number. manufacturer - The manufacturer of this object. name - The name of this object version - The version of this object codeset - The Code set of this object. customerName - The name of the customer this object was created for. defaultGW - The default gateway used when accessing this object. discoveredDate - The date when this object was first discovered. facilityName - The name of the facility housing this object. locale - The locale this object is in. lockComment - The comment on this object's locked. NOTE\: object may not be locked. lockDate - The date this object was last locked. lockUser - The user who locked this object last. isLocked - A boolean value specifying whether or not this object is currently locked. loopbackIP - The loopback ip address used by this object. managementIP - The management ip address used by this object. mid - mid The server's management identifier. NetBIOSName - The full netBIOS (Windows networking) name for this object. lifecycle - The state in the Opsware lifecycle that this object is currently in. origin - The origin of the managed server. ASSIMILATED or PROVISIONED osFlavor - The flavor of the OS running on this object. For example\: Windows. osSPVersion - The service pack version of the OS running on the object. peerIP - The managed server's peer IP address. platformName - The name of the platform. previousSWRegDate -The last time the Opsware agent reported the installed software on the server. realmName - The name of the realm this object is in. stage - The stage of the managed server. state - The current state of the managed server\: OK, UNREACHABLE or MAINTENANCE use - The intended use of the managed server (i.e. its role in a deployment)\: DEVELOPMENT, STAGING, PRODUCTION or UNKNOWN. virtualizationType - The virtualization type. b81a56db-917c-4509-83b0-4e8751ef4b3c.cc7f9956-46d0-4b2c-84a8-be41e88b4f69.description=Sleeps for "X" seconds. 
Inputs\:
seconds - The number of seconds to sleep.

Responses\:
success - Slept for "X" seconds.
failure - was unable to sleep for some reason
b81a56db-917c-4509-83b0-4e8751ef4b3c.d5bd6e10-4829-4acf-809c-276459bc319e.description=Counts from one number to another number. 
Inputs\:
count - number of loops to complete
reset - If true, then the counter will restart counting from the beginning.

Returns\:
The number that was just counted.

Responses\:
has more - Not yet done counting.
no more - Done counting. This will only be returned once, then counting restarts.
failure - Something went wrong.

flow.name: SA_SyncAgentWithHostname

step.name: Find Server in SA by hostname (ogfs)

staticBinding.value: /opsw/api/com/opsware/server/ServerService/method/.findServerRefs:i filter="device:((device_agent_status IN "OK")&(device_hostname BEGINS_WITH "${server.hostname}"))" || ( echo "Failed to find server by hostname - ${server.hostname}" && exit 1 )

step.name: Change SA name to hostname by mid (ogfs)

staticBinding.value: echo -n "${sa.hostname}" > /opsw/.Server.ID/${saMid}/attr/name || ( echo "Failed to set SA agent name to ${sa.hostname}" && exit 1 )
